<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The Zend_Queue_Stomp_Client_Connection accepts an options array as 4th parameter for the open method. This options array is not used by the stomp client. This cause a problem with the timeout setting for Activemq adapter(and probably all other stomp related adapters). The timeout option is never set, so the const READ_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT_SEC is always used by the connection.</p>

<p>From Zend_Queue_Stomp_Client_Connection
public function open($scheme, $host, $port, array $options = array())</p>

<p>Invoked as follows
$connection-&gt;open($scheme, $host, $port)</p>

